# A small [[fly]]ing [[mammal]] ([[bat]]) of [[South America]] which uses its [[sharp]] [[incisor]] [[teeth]] to nick the foot of a [[large]] animal ([[e.g.]] a [[cow]]) while the animal is [[asleep]], allowing it to [[surreptitiously]] [[lap]] a [[blood]] [[meal]].  Its [[saliva]] contains an [[anticoagulant]] to keep the blood flowing during feeding.


